{"questionId":"9082858","questionHtml":"<p>Show that the energy dissipated in the loop from <em>t </em>= 0 to <em>t </em>= 3.5 s is 0.13 J.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Energy is being dissipated for 0.50 s&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>F</mi><mi>v</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>=</mo></math>«<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>13</mn></math> J»</p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>V</mi><mi>l</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>33</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>=</mo></math>«<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>13</mn></math> J»&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Allow <strong>ECF</strong> from <strong>(b)</strong> and <strong>(c)</strong>. </em></p>\n<p><em>Watch for candidates who do not justify somehow the use of 0.5 s and just divide by 2 their answer.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9082858","referenceCode":"21N.2.SL.TZ0.d.i","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Show that the energy dissipated in the loop from t = 0 to t = 3.5 s is 0.13 J.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["B. The particulate nature of matter","B.5 Current and circuits","A. Space, time and motion","A.3 Work, energy and power"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}